<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="503" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,654,1759]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1554,1579]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[609,716,1555,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Afrobethylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bapedi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[609,716,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">A. bapedi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[724,814,1554,1579]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[724,814,1554,1579]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by having the area between anterior margin of eye and demarcation of median clypeal lobe clearly concave, the vertex crest straight, and with thick setae absent, the mesoscutellum extending beyond anterior margin of metapostnotum, and the forewing with flexion lines not forming a rectangular area. However this species has the forewing with 
<number box="[958,973,1663,1687]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="2.0">2</number>
R 
<number box="[995,1005,1663,1687]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="1.0">1</number>
cell not forming a right angle, and the genitalia with the sting only slightly longer than the body of genitalia, whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[1038,1145,1699,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Afrobethylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bapedi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1038,1145,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">A. bapedi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1153,1242,1698,1723]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1153,1242,1698,1723]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has the forewing with 
<number box="[208,223,1735,1759]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="2.0">2</number>
R 
<number box="[245,255,1735,1759]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="1.0">1</number>
cell forming a right angle, and the female the sting as long as the body of genitalia.
</paragraph>
